    <text id="B1066T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Garrick Mallery submits a copy of excerpts of John McDonnell's District report.
                    The excerpts concern the compilation of marriage registers and the apparent lack
                    of appropriate forms for such purposes.</p>
            </div1>
            <div1 type="section" id="wrapper">
                <p>Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees">R.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Freedmen">F.</abbr> &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned">A.</abbr>
                    Lands, State of Virginia, Office Chief <abbr
                        expan="Quartermaster Disbursing Officer">Qr.Msr. D.O.</abbr>, Richmond <abbr
                        expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>, May 8, 1867<lb/>Respectfully returned to <abbr
                        expan="Brevet Brigadier">Bvt. Brig.</abbr> General O. Brown <abbr
                        expan="Assistant">Asst</abbr> Commissioner with the information that
                        <unclear>975</unclear> Registry blanks for Registering marriages were sent
                    to Captain Lacey (then in charge of Captain McDonnell's District) on July 19th
                    1866. Blanks have been ordered such this day.<lb/>(signed) Ger White<lb/>Brevet
                    Major Chief <abbr expan="Quartermaster Disbursing Officer">Qr.Mast.
                D.O.</abbr></p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d5">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d6">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees, Freedmen and <abbr expan="Abandoned Lands"
                        >A.L.</abbr><lb/>Office <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub Asst
                            Comr</abbr>, 9th District, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bvt. Brig.
                        Gen'l.</abbr> O. Brown<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst.
                        Comr</abbr>, State of Virginia<lb/>Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-04-30">April 30th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>General:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>In accordance with Circular No. 5, dated Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees"
                        >R.</abbr><abbr expan="Freedmen">F.</abbr> &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned"
                        >A.</abbr> Lands, Head Quarters, <abbr expan="Assistant">Asst.</abbr>
                    Commissioner, State of <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>, Richmond, <abbr
                        expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>, March 27th, 1867, I have visited the Counties
                    comprising the 9th <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                    >Va</abbr>, and have the honor to make the following report.</p>

                <p>(Extract)</p>

                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Counties of Frederick and Clark</hi>
                </p>

                <p>"A Register of Marriages has been commenced in Frederick County, but want of
                    blanks prevents its completion. In Clark County, nothing has yet been done in
                    the matter, but will as soon as practicable."</p>

                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Counties of Warren and Page</hi>
                </p>

                <p>"No register of Marriages has yet been made in either county, and no blanks were
                    ever furnished for that purpose."</p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Shenandoah and Rockingham <abbr expan="Counties"
                        >Co's</abbr></hi>
                </p>

                <p>"A register of Marriages has been made for both counties, but not on the Bureau
                    blanks, which have not been furnished."</p>

                <p>
                    <hi rend="underline">Augusta and Highland <abbr expan="Counties"
                    >Co's.</abbr></hi>
                </p>

                <p>"A complete register of Marriages has been made for the County of Augusta, but
                    not on the Bureau blanks. As yet no Register has been made for Highland County."</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Respectfully submitted</salute>
                    <signed>(signed) John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr
                            expan="Captain Veterans' Reserve Corps">Capt V.R.C.</abbr><lb/><abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">Sub. Asst. Comr.</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Official copy furnished for the information of <abbr
                            expan="Brevet Major">Bvt. Maj.</abbr> Geo. White, <abbr
                            expan="Chief Quartermaster">Chf QM</abbr> &amp;c and for report as
                        to the reason why the blanks have not been furnished.<lb/>Garrick
                            Mallery<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> 43<hi rend="super">d</hi>
                        <abbr expan="Infantry">Infty</abbr>, A.A.A.G.<lb/>Richmond, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr><lb/>6th May. 1867</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
